{
  "texts": [
    "China must establish clear guidelines for STEM curricula, resource development, and teacher training, mainly supporting underserved groups (Dong et al. 2020).",
    "Ensuring these groups access STEM education creates a more inclusive and equitable learning environment (Han and Appelbaum, 2018a, 2018b).",
    "A solid foundation with top-level planning is essential for advancing STEM education in China.",
    "With well-structured and adequately supported professional development initiatives, China can progress from its nascent stage to a more mature, integrated STEM educational landscape, setting an example for other developing nations (Nadelson and Seifert, 2017).",
    "Related Studies."
  ]
}